<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t16880831-35">
               <interp inst="t16880831-35" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t16880831-35" type="year" value="1688"></interp>
               <interp inst="t16880831-35" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/16880831"></interp>
               <interp inst="t16880831-35" type="date" value="16880831"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16880831-35-off179-c120" targOrder="Y" targets="t16880831-35-defend183 t16880831-35-off179 t16880831-35-verdict182"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16880831-35-off179-c121" targOrder="Y" targets="t16880831-35-defend185 t16880831-35-off179 t16880831-35-verdict183"></join>
         
               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16880831-35-defend183" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Gerrard
                  <interp inst="t16880831-35-defend183" type="surname" value="Gerrard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16880831-35-defend183" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16880831-35-defend183" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             and 
               
                  <persName id="t16880831-35-defend185" type="defendantName">
                     James 
                     Pidgley
                  <interp inst="t16880831-35-defend185" type="surname" value="Pidgley"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16880831-35-defend185" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16880831-35-defend185" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , were both Indicted for <rs id="t16880831-35-off179" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16880831-35-off179" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16880831-35-off179" type="offenceSubcategory" value="animalTheft"></interp>
               stealing on the <rs id="t16880831-35-cd180" type="crimeDate">27th. of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16880831-35-off179 t16880831-35-cd180"></join> last, one brown Gelding, value 7 l. and one other Gelding, price 7 l.
            </rs> the Goods and Chattels of 
               
                  <persName id="t16880831-35-victim187" type="victimName">
                     Edward 
                     Speare
                  <interp inst="t16880831-35-victim187" type="surname" value="Speare"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16880831-35-victim187" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16880831-35-victim187" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16880831-35-off179 t16880831-35-victim187"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            . It appeared upon their Tryal that they were taken at Bristol offering the Geldings to Sale; Pidgley Sold them and Gerrard was the Voucher, which Mr. Speare Swore plainly against them; how that they were lost out of his Grounds at <placeName id="t16880831-35-crimeloc181">Hammersmith</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t16880831-35-crimeloc181" type="placeName" value="Hammersmith"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t16880831-35-crimeloc181" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16880831-35-off179 t16880831-35-crimeloc181"></join>; and when the Prisoners were Apprehended, they said that they found them in the High-way; but Gerrard having not so strong an Evidence against him, he was <rs id="t16880831-35-verdict182" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16880831-35-verdict182" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               Cleared
            </rs>, but Pidgley was found <rs id="t16880831-35-verdict183" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16880831-35-verdict183" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               guilty
            </rs> of Felony.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t16880831-35-punish184" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16880831-35-punish184" type="punishmentCategory" value="death"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t16880831-35-defend183 t16880831-35-punish184"></join>
               
                     <note>[Death. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
